        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 20 at 2:36PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 236 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Conrad, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ledger.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
